[SN]TITLE[SN]
Instagram boss on pitching to the Pope

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Image-sharing network Instagram has announced it now has 500 million active users - with 300 million logging on at least once a day.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
21 June 2016 Last updated at 14:01 BST
It's the app that really kickstarted the selfie craze, but has recently faced user backlash over changes to both its logo and the algorithm that is used to decide the order images are displayed.
Co-founder and chief executive Kevin Systrom sat down with our North America technology reporter Dave Lee to discuss convincing the Pope to join and other growth tactics.
